Serves 5 – 6 You’ll need: 800g-900g beef strips; 80ml oil; 900ml stir-fry vegetable mix; 1 pouch Royco Cape Malay Curry Wet Cook-in Sauce (415g); 60ml roasted cashew nuts, chopped; 40ml fresh coriander leaves How to: Brown beef in batches in a little hot oil and set aside. Stir-fry the vegetables in a little more oil for 3-4 minutes. Add the beef and the contents of the pouch of Royco Cape Malay Curry Wet Cook-in Sauce, and stir-fry for 1 minute. Add the cashew nuts and serve garnished with coriander leaves. * Chicken strips can also be used for this recipe. *Recipe and image by Royco.